\pard\fs24\lang2057\f1\fs27\cf1\b\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q1.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 Symbol Puzzle\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Symbol Puzzle is a simple puzzle where the user places symbols into a grid, trying to maximise their score as they do so.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The user is allowed to place a specified number of symbols (38 in the standard puzzle) into the grid. The puzzle is finished when the last symbol has been placed.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 To score points, the user must place symbols into cells in the grid so that they match a pattern. In the standard puzzle the user is able to use the symbols \f2\fs20\sb0 Q\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 T\f1\fs22\sb240  and \f2\fs20\sb0 X\f1\fs22\sb240 .\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 To score 10 points using the symbol \f2\fs20\sb0 Q\f1\fs22\sb240  the user needs to place five \f2\fs20\sb0 Q\f1\fs22\sb240  symbols in a 3\'d73 section of the grid so that they match the pattern shown in \b Figure 1\b0 .\par
\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0{\pict\jpegblip\picw1815\pich2085\picwgoal1815\pichgoal2085\picscalex100\picscaley100
}\~\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 To score 10 points using the symbol \f2\fs20\sb0 T\f1\fs22\sb240  the user needs to place five \f2\fs20\sb0 T\f1\fs22\sb240  symbols in a 3\'d73 section of the grid so that they match the pattern shown in \b Figure 2\b0 .\par
\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0{\pict\jpegblip\picw1665\pich2040\picwgoal1665\pichgoal2040\picscalex100\picscaley100
}\~\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 To score 10 points using the symbol \f2\fs20\sb0 X\f1\fs22\sb240  the user needs to place five \f2\fs20\sb0 X\f1\fs22\sb240  symbols in a 3\'d73 section of the grid so that they match the pattern shown in \b Figure 3\b0 .\par
\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0{\pict\jpegblip\picw1770\pich2145\picwgoal1770\pichgoal2145\picscalex100\picscaley100
}\~\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 When the user has successfully created one of the allowed patterns within a 3\'d73 section of the grid, they are no longer allowed to place the symbol used in that pattern in any of the other cells in that 3\'d73 section. However, other symbols can still be placed in empty cells within that 3\'d73 section.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Some cells are blocked, denoted by the symbol @. The user is not able to place a symbol in a blocked cell. In the standard puzzle, the number of blocked cells and the position of each blocked cell is generated randomly.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 An example of a starting grid for the standard puzzle is shown in \b Figure 4\b0 .\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The row and column numbers have been shown. The cell in the bottom right corner of the grid is row 1, column 8\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li0\ri0 \~\par

